West Pokot woman representative Regina Nyeris and Sigor MP Phillip Rotino yesterday ditched Jubilee Party for Chama Cha Mashinani.The two were received by CCM leader and Bomet Governor Isaac Rutto.The two accused Jubilee of lack of fairness and transparency ahead of the primaries in West Pokot today.They spoke to the press at a Nairobi hotel.&ldquo;We are here to announce that we have officially joined Chama Cha Mashinani and we will not be participating in the Jubilee nominations today,&rdquo; Rotino said.He said he made the decision to ditch Jubilee, because &ldquo;the party has preferred candidates&rdquo;. &ldquo;I cannot participate in a fraudulent exercise. We know the party has decided on its list of aspirants. I want to meet my competitors at the ballot on August 8.&rdquo;